                        <li><i class="fab fa-spotify"></i> <strong>Example:</strong> Spotify's squad metrics and OKRs
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="speaker-notes">
                    Vroom's Expectancy Theory is highly applicable in digital environments where performance can be
                    measured precisely. Expectancy is enhanced when digital tools provide clear feedback on
                    effort-performance relationships, as seen with GitHub's contribution metrics that visually show
                    coding activity. Instrumentality benefits from digital transparency in performance tracking and
                    reward allocation, like Stack Overflow's reputation system that clearly links contributions to
                    recognition. Valence can be personalized using data analytics to understand individual preferences,
                    allowing for customized rewards. Spotify uses squad metrics and OKRs (Objectives and Key Results) to
                    create clear performance-reward linkages. Digital platforms enable real-time performance tracking,
                    clear goal setting, and transparent reward systems that strengthen all three components of
                    expectancy theory.
                </div>
            </div>

